{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 11:11:33.597951", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nOverview\\n- Topology: 1 super-spine (AS 65000), 2 spines, 2 leaves, 2 hosts. All routing via EBGP. Links are /31s in 172.16.0.0/16; leaf-to-host subnets are 10.0.0.0/24 and 10.0.1.0/24.\\n- High-level status: End-to-end host connectivity is up with low latency and zero loss. However, there is a control-plane anomaly: one spine is not participating in BGP due to an AS-number mismatch, reducing redundancy.\\n\\nEnd-to-End Reachability\\n- pc_0_0 -> pc_0_1: 0% loss, RTT avg ~3.6 ms.\\n- pc_0_1 -> pc_0_0: 0% loss, RTT avg ~1.9 ms.\\n- Interpretation: Data-plane forwarding between hosts is currently healthy.\\n\\nControl-Plane (BGP) and Routing State\\n\\nLeaves\\n- leaf_router_0_0 (AS 65200)\\n  - BGP neighbors:\\n    - 172.16.0.4 (spine_router_0_0, AS 65100): Established, PfxRcd=1.\\n    - 172.16.0.8 (spine_router_0_1, expected AS 65101): State Active (down).\\n  - Routes: Connected 10.0.0.0/24; learns 10.0.1.0/24 via 172.16.0.4.\\n- leaf_router_0_1 (AS 65201)\\n  - BGP neighbors:\\n    - 172.16.0.6 (spine_router_0_0, AS 65100): Established, PfxRcd=1.\\n    - 172.16.0.10 (spine_router_0_1, expected AS 65101): State Active (down).\\n  - Routes: Connected 10.0.1.0/24; learns 10.0.0.0/24 via 172.16.0.6.\\n\\nSpines\\n- spine_router_0_0 (AS 65100)\\n  - BGP neighbors:\\n    - 172.16.0.0 (super_spine, AS 65000): Established.\\n    - 172.16.0.5 (leaf_0_0, AS 65200): Established, PfxRcd=1.\\n    - 172.16.0.7 (leaf_0_1, AS 65201): Established, PfxRcd=1.\\n  - Routes: Has 10.0.0.0/24 via leaf_0_0 and 10.0.1.0/24 via leaf_0_1.\\n- spine_router_0_1\\n  - Local AS configured: 65701 (from running config).\\n  - BGP neighbors (configured remote AS):\\n    - 172.16.0.2 (super_spine, AS 65000): State Idle.\\n    - 172.16.0.9 (leaf_0_0, AS 65200): State Idle.\\n    - 172.16.0.11 (leaf_0_1, AS 65201): State Idle.\\n  - Routes: Only connected subnets present; no BGP-learned 10.0.x.0/24 routes.\\n  - Note: All neighbor sessions fail to establish (Idle), consistent with AS-number mismatch.\\n  \\nSuper-spine\\n- super_spine_router_0 (AS 65000)\\n  - BGP neighbors:\\n    - 172.16.0.1 (spine_0_0, AS 65100): Established, PfxRcd=2.\\n    - 172.16.0.3 (spine_0_1, expected AS 65101): State Active (down).\\n  - Routes: 10.0.0.0/24 and 10.0.1.0/24 both via 172.16.0.1 (spine_0_0).\\n\\nAnomalies Detected\\n- BGP sessions to spine_router_0_1 are down from all adjacent devices (both leaves and the super-spine report Active/Idle states for that neighbor).\\n- spine_router_0_1’s running configuration shows local AS 65701:\\n  - router bgp 65701\\n- All adjacent devices expect spine_router_0_1 to be in AS 65101:\\n  - Leaves neighbor remote-as 65101 for 172.16.0.8 and 172.16.0.10.\\n  - Super-spine neighbor remote-as 65101 for 172.16.0.3.\\n\\nFault Localization\\n- Faulty device: spine_router_0_1.\\n- Fault domain: Control-plane (BGP) configuration on the spine.\\n\\nRoot Cause\\n- Misconfigured BGP local AS on spine_router_0_1 (65701 instead of the expected 65101). This AS mismatch prevents EBGP session establishment with the super-spine and both leaves. As a result, spine_router_0_1 learns no leaf prefixes and is not used for forwarding.\\n\\nImpact Assessment\\n- Current traffic still flows successfully via spine_router_0_0, maintaining host connectivity and reachability to both 10.0.0.0/24 and 10.0.1.0/24.\\n- However, the fabric has lost redundancy and potential load-sharing. If spine_router_0_0 fails, connectivity between the two leaf subnets would be lost. Additionally, the super-spine only has paths via spine_router_0_0, reducing resiliency.\\n\\nKey Evidence (selected)\\n- super_spine_router_0 “show bgp summary”: neighbor 172.16.0.3 (spine_0_1) Active; PfxRcd=0.\\n- spine_router_0_1 “show bgp summary”: all neighbors Idle; PfxRcd=0.\\n- spine_router_0_1 “show running-config”: router bgp 65701 (mismatch).\\n- Leaves “show bgp summary”: neighbors to 65101 (172.16.0.8/10) Active, while neighbors to 65100 (172.16.0.4/6) Established.\\n- Route tables: spine_router_0_1 lacks 10.0.0.0/24 and 10.0.1.0/24; others have the expected routes via spine_router_0_0., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='8ea0673e-7d85-4b19-89c9-8a236b911fc8'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
